{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}
{% import "partials/_demo.njk" as ui %}

{% block title %}App shell · Stisla{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <header>
    <h1>App shell</h1>
    <p class="lead">The page-level frame that positions a sidebar next to a main content column.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <p>The shell composes <code>.sidebar</code> and <code>.app-shell__main</code> into a layout. It owns where the pieces sit and how the layout responds to viewport size. Sidebar and navbar internals live on their own pages. Demos below use placeholder slots in place of the rich panels.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic</h2>
    <p><code>.app-shell</code> wraps a <code>.sidebar</code> and an <code>.app-shell__main</code>. The shell sets the sidebar's width via <code>--app-shell-sidebar-width</code> (default <code>16rem</code>), and main fills the rest with <code>flex-grow: 1</code>.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="app-shell overflow-hidden" style="border: 1px solid var(--st-border); border-radius: var(--st-radius); min-height: 0; transform: translate(0); height: 22rem;">
      <aside class="d-flex flex-wrap sidebar align-items-center justify-content-center text-muted-foreground fs-2" style="background: var(--st-surface-2); border-right: 1px solid var(--st-border);">Sidebar</aside>
      <main class="app-shell__main" style="padding: 1rem">
        <h3 class="h6">Dashboard</h3>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">Page content goes here.</p>
      </main>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
    <p>The demo overrides the shell's height for preview purposes. In production, drop the inline style and the default <code>min-height: 100vh</code> fills the viewport.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>With top navbar</h2>
    <p>Add a direct <code>.navbar</code> child to the shell and wrap the sidebar and main in an <code>.app-shell__body</code>. The shell auto-detects this shape via <code>:has()</code> and switches to flex-column. No modifier class needed.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="app-shell overflow-hidden" style="border: 1px solid var(--st-border); border-radius: var(--st-radius); min-height: 0; transform: translate(0); height: 24rem;">
      <nav class="navbar text-muted-foreground fs-2" style="background: var(--st-surface-2); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--st-border); padding-block: 0.75rem; padding-inline: 1rem">Navbar</nav>
      <div class="app-shell__body">
        <aside class="d-flex flex-wrap sidebar align-items-center justify-content-center text-muted-foreground fs-2" style="background: var(--st-surface-2); border-right: 1px solid var(--st-border);">Sidebar</aside>
        <main class="app-shell__main" style="padding: 1rem">
          <h3 class="h6">Dashboard</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">Page content goes here.</p>
        </main>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}

    <h3>Navbar inside the main column</h3>
    <p>To keep the sidebar at the full page height with its own brand, leave the shell as a flex-row and put the navbar inside <code>.app-shell__main</code>. The navbar never extends across the sidebar.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="app-shell overflow-hidden" style="border: 1px solid var(--st-border); border-radius: var(--st-radius); min-height: 0; transform: translate(0); height: 24rem;">
      <aside class="d-flex flex-wrap sidebar align-items-center justify-content-center text-muted-foreground fs-2" style="background: var(--st-surface-2); border-right: 1px solid var(--st-border);">Sidebar</aside>
      <main class="app-shell__main">
        <nav class="navbar text-muted-foreground fs-2" style="background: var(--st-surface-2); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--st-border); padding-block: 0.75rem; padding-inline: 1rem">Navbar</nav>
        <div class="flex-fill" style="padding: 1rem">
          <h3 class="h6">Dashboard</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">Page content goes here.</p>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>With footer</h2>
    <p>Drop a <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code> at the end of <code>.app-shell__main</code>. Main is already a flex column, so <code>margin-top: auto</code> on the footer pushes it to the bottom even when content is short.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="app-shell overflow-hidden" style="border: 1px solid var(--st-border); border-radius: var(--st-radius); min-height: 0; transform: translate(0); height: 22rem;">
      <aside class="d-flex flex-wrap sidebar align-items-center justify-content-center text-muted-foreground fs-2" style="background: var(--st-surface-2); border-right: 1px solid var(--st-border);">Sidebar</aside>
      <main class="app-shell__main">
        <div style="padding: 1rem">
          <h3 class="h6">Dashboard</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">Page content goes here.</p>
        </div>
        <footer class="fs-2 text-muted-foreground mt-auto" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--st-border); padding-block: 0.75rem; padding-inline: 1rem">
          &copy; 2026 Acme. Built with Stisla.
        </footer>
      </main>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Sticky sidebar</h2>
    <p>The shell defaults to <code>min-height: 100vh</code>. When the page is taller than the viewport, the window scrolls and the sidebar scrolls with it. To pin the sidebar to the viewport top, add four inline styles to <code>.sidebar</code>.</p>
    {% call ui.code() %}
    <div class="app-shell">
      <aside class="sidebar" style="
        position: sticky;
        top: 0;
        height: 100vh;
        align-self: flex-start;
      ">
        <!-- ... -->
      </aside>
      <main class="app-shell__main">
        <!-- long content here; the window scrolls, the sidebar stays put -->
      </main>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
    <p>For a Gmail-style locked shell (no window scroll, main is the scroll container), use <code>height: 100vh; overflow: hidden</code> on the shell and <code>overflow: auto</code> on main. Both patterns are opt-in via inline style, and the shell stays out of the way.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Desktop collapse (rail)</h2>
    <p>Add <code>.is-sidebar-collapsed</code> to <code>.app-shell</code> to swap the sidebar to its rail width (<code>--app-shell-sidebar-width-collapsed</code>, default <code>4.25rem</code>). Pair it with <code>.is-collapsed</code> on the sidebar itself for the rail visuals. Any button can wire the toggle with <code>data-stisla-app-shell-toggle="collapse"</code>. <code>Stisla.AppShell</code> delegates the rail flip to the descendant <code>Stisla.Sidebar</code> instance so its rail visuals, ARIA, and submenu close-on-collapse stay in sync.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="app-shell overflow-hidden" data-stisla-app-shell style="border: 1px solid var(--st-border); border-radius: var(--st-radius); min-height: 0; transform: translate(0); height: 22rem;">
      <aside class="d-flex flex-wrap sidebar align-items-center justify-content-center text-muted-foreground fs-2" style="background: var(--st-surface-2); border-right: 1px solid var(--st-border);">Sidebar</aside>
      <main class="app-shell__main">
        <nav style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--st-border); padding-block: 0.5rem; padding-inline: 0.75rem">
          <button class="btn btn--ghost btn--neutral btn--icon-only btn--compact" type="button" data-stisla-app-shell-toggle="collapse" aria-label="Toggle sidebar">
            <i data-lucide="panel-left"></i>
          </button>
        </nav>
        <div class="flex-fill" style="padding: 1rem">
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">Click the icon to collapse the sidebar to a rail.</p>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Mobile drawer</h2>
    <p>Below the <code>lg</code> breakpoint, the sidebar leaves the flex flow and sits fixed off-screen. Setting <code>.is-sidebar-visible</code> on the shell slides it in and shows a backdrop. Any button can flip the class with <code>data-stisla-app-shell-toggle="visibility"</code>. Backdrop clicks and the Escape key dismiss the drawer. Opt out per shell with <code>{ dismissOnBackdrop: false }</code> or <code>{ dismissOnEscape: false }</code> via <code>data-stisla-app-shell-opts</code>.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="app-shell overflow-hidden" data-stisla-app-shell style="border: 1px solid var(--st-border); border-radius: var(--st-radius); min-height: 0; transform: translate(0); height: 22rem;">
      <aside class="d-flex flex-wrap sidebar align-items-center justify-content-center text-muted-foreground fs-2" style="background: var(--st-surface-2); border-right: 1px solid var(--st-border);">Sidebar</aside>
      <main class="app-shell__main">
        <nav style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--st-border); padding-block: 0.5rem; padding-inline: 0.75rem">
          <button class="btn btn--ghost btn--neutral btn--icon-only btn--compact" type="button" data-stisla-app-shell-toggle="visibility" aria-label="Open sidebar">
            <i data-lucide="menu"></i>
          </button>
        </nav>
        <div class="flex-fill" style="padding: 1rem">
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">Resize the browser below <code>lg</code> (992px) and tap the menu icon. A backdrop covers the rest of the shell while open; tap anywhere outside the sidebar or press <kbd>Esc</kbd> to dismiss.</p>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Auto toggle (responsive)</h2>
    <p><code>data-stisla-app-shell-toggle="auto"</code> picks the right action per viewport. <code>visibility</code> below the <code>lg</code> breakpoint, <code>collapse</code> above. Use this for the single hamburger or menu button most dashboards ship in their top bar. The trigger's <code>aria-expanded</code> tracks whichever state matches the current viewport and re-syncs when the user resizes across the breakpoint. Call <code>Stisla.AppShell.getOrCreate(shell).toggleSidebarAuto()</code> for the programmatic equivalent.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="app-shell overflow-hidden" data-stisla-app-shell style="border: 1px solid var(--st-border); border-radius: var(--st-radius); min-height: 0; transform: translate(0); height: 22rem;">
      <aside class="d-flex flex-wrap sidebar align-items-center justify-content-center text-muted-foreground fs-2" style="background: var(--st-surface-2); border-right: 1px solid var(--st-border);">Sidebar</aside>
      <main class="app-shell__main">
        <nav style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--st-border); padding-block: 0.5rem; padding-inline: 0.75rem">
          <button class="btn btn--ghost btn--neutral btn--icon-only btn--compact" type="button" data-stisla-app-shell-toggle="auto" aria-label="Toggle sidebar">
            <i data-lucide="panel-left"></i>
          </button>
        </nav>
        <div class="flex-fill" style="padding: 1rem">
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">On desktop, the icon rails the sidebar. On mobile, it opens the drawer.</p>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Customization</h2>
    <p>Override any of these on a <code>.app-shell</code> instance (inline style, a wrapper class, a <code>[data-theme]</code> block) to retune that shell. The outer wrapper and the main column carry their own bg + color so a heavier chrome (gray surrounds, white main) is one-liner away.</p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Variable</th><th>Use</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>--app-shell-bg</code></td><td>Outer wrapper background</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--app-shell-color</code></td><td>Outer wrapper text color</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--app-shell-main-bg</code></td><td>Main column background</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--app-shell-main-color</code></td><td>Main column text color</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--app-shell-sidebar-width</code></td><td>Desktop sidebar width</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--app-shell-sidebar-width-collapsed</code></td><td>Desktop collapsed (rail) width</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--app-shell-sidebar-mobile-bg</code></td><td>Mobile drawer surface (opaque so content underneath doesn't bleed through)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--app-shell-sidebar-mobile-shadow</code></td><td>Drawer shadow, cast right-ward to signal the slide-from-left motion</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--app-shell-sidebar-z-index</code></td><td>Z-index of the mobile drawer; the backdrop sits one below</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--app-shell-backdrop-bg</code></td><td>Mobile backdrop color (fixed-dark in both themes)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--app-shell-transition-duration</code></td><td>Width and slide transition speed</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>
{% endblock %}
